const title = "Follett Ice Machine Repair Los Angeles — Same Day";
const description = "Follett ice machine repair across SoCal. Healthcare + restaurants. Chewblet nugget, Symphony Plus. BHGS #A49573, EPA 608 universal. $120 commercial dx.";

const faqs = [
  {
    q: "Is Follett the same brand as Scotsman or Manitowoc?",
    a: "No. Follett is an independent Pennsylvania manufacturer based in Easton, PA, founded in 1948. They are not part of Welbilt (Manitowoc), Ali Group (Scotsman, Ice-O-Matic), or Hoshizaki Corporation. Follett's specialty is chewable Chewblet ice and healthcare/laboratory ice dispensers. Their distribution and service network is smaller than the big three (Hoshizaki, Manitowoc, Scotsman) which means parts can take 3 to 7 days on uncommon items."
  },
  {
    q: "What is Chewblet ice and why is it a Follett specialty?",
    a: "Chewblet is Follett's proprietary chewable nugget-format ice produced by an extruded auger system rather than the cube-mold method used by Hoshizaki KM-Edge or Manitowoc Indigo cubers. The result is soft, chewable ice that healthcare facilities prefer (patients with mouth sensitivity, post-surgical, hydration compliance) and that some restaurants and beverage operations specify for premium drinks. Follett didn't invent chewable nugget ice (Scotsman Brilliance and Manitowoc R-Series compete), but Follett's healthcare-focused engineering gives Chewblet a strong position in hospitals and clinics."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you service Follett Symphony Plus and Maestro Plus dispensers?",
    a: "Yes. Symphony Plus is Follett's healthcare-focused ice and water dispenser line, common in hospital patient floors, dialysis units, and assisted-living facilities. Maestro Plus is the restaurant and beverage equivalent. Both share core mechanical components (auger, dispense valve, drip tray, control board) but Symphony Plus adds additional sanitization features (UV options, antimicrobial agitator) for healthcare environments. We service both lines including the Sanitizer 2.0 cleaning cycle on newer Symphony Plus units."
  },
  {
    q: "Are Follett ice machines worth the premium for a restaurant operation?",
    a: "Depends on whether your customers care about chewable ice. If your menu features cocktails or premium beverages where ice texture is part of the value proposition, Chewblet on a Follett 7Series or 25Series compact countertop dispenser is a reasonable specification. If you're running a typical restaurant where ice is just ice, Follett's premium position over Manitowoc Indigo or Hoshizaki KM-Edge probably doesn't pencil out. Healthcare and laboratory operations where chewable ice is functionally required almost always specify Follett."
  },
  {
    q: "What's the typical Follett service call?",
    a: "Most Follett service calls in our LA service area are healthcare facilities (Cedars-Sinai outpatient clinics, UCLA Medical Center facilities, Kaiser locations, dialysis centers across LA and Orange County) and the failure modes are different from restaurant ice machines. Common: auger gear motor failure on Chewblet units (year 5 to 8), dispense valve actuator wear, control board on older Symphony units (year 8 to 12), water inlet valve, condenser coil cleaning. Less common: compressor or full sealed-system work, because Follett units in healthcare see steady-state operation rather than the on-off cycling that stresses restaurant ice machines."
  },
  {
    q: "What's the parts availability on Follett?",
    a: "Mixed. Common service parts (auger drive components, dispense valves, control boards on current models, cleaning chemicals, gaskets) are stocked through Follett's Easton PA distribution and typically arrive in 3 to 5 days. Less common parts (older Symphony control boards, specialty Chewblet auger flights, Maestro vintage components) can take 1 to 2 weeks on backorder. We pre-confirm parts availability when we diagnose so you have an accurate timeline before authorizing the repair."
  },
  {
    q: "What's your warranty on Follett repairs?",
    a: "Ninety days SDAR labor and parts on the work we perform. Follett component warranties are processed separately through Follett's Easton PA service network. We help process warranty claims when applicable so you don't pay for parts that should be covered. BHGS #A49573, EPA 608 Universal #1346255700410, BBB Accredited Business."
  }
];

